cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses device-to-device (D2D) communications in wireless cellular networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper derives the equilibrium cumulative distribution function (CDF) of the D2D transmit power using stochastic geometry, which involves mathematical modeling and analysis, and thus, can be categorized under information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with controlling the interference brought to the macro-cellular user equipment (UE) in D2D transmissions, which can be viewed as a control problem in systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the uplink transmission of D2D users, which can involve multimedia content such as video, audio, etc. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper does not explicitly discuss cryptography and security, but D2D communications can have implications for security and privacy, and thus, can be categorized under cryptography and security.
